message:
The most interesting sunsets are the ones slightly obstructed by clouds. This was the case for us in San Juan, Siquijor when we witnessed one of the most stunning and memorable sunsets for us. The partly cloudy day produced a scarlet sky as the sunlight faded. Of course, beautiful sunsets are best enjoyed with family and friends, and an ice cold bottle of beer.

Words and Video by Christer Isulat
@filipino_flight_tales

